VALUES
(43, 7, 32, 44, 5, 26, 26, 'the people murmured such things', 'Authority and Fear of the People', 'Both passages emphasize the role of authorities responding to public sentiment. In John, the Pharisees send officers due to the people''s murmuring, while in Acts, the captain and officers act cautiously, fearing the people.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 32, 40, 23, 13, 13, 'the Pharisees and the chief priests', 'Opposition to Jesus'' Ministry', 'This connection highlights the opposition faced by Jesus from the Pharisees, as seen in both passages. In John 7:32, the Pharisees send officers to take him, while in Matthew 23:13, they are condemned for hindering others from entering the kingdom.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 33, 43, 13, 33, 33, 'Yet a little while am I with you', 'Jesus'' Temporary Presence', 'Both passages emphasize the temporary nature of Jesus'' presence among his followers. The phrase ''a little while'' in both verses highlights the urgency of his impending departure.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 33, 43, 16, 5, 5, 'go unto him that sent me', 'Jesus'' Departure Announcement', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' impending departure, indicating he will return to the one who sent him. The phrase ''go unto him that sent me'' appears in both verses, highlighting the continuity of his mission and the significance of his going away.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 33, 41, 16, 19, 19, 'I go unto him that sent me', 'Jesus'' Departure and Ascension', 'This connection highlights Jesus'' statement about his impending departure in John 7:33, where he mentions going to ''him that sent me.'' Mark 16:19 describes the fulfillment of this departure as Jesus is received into heaven, emphasizing the completion of his mission.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 33, 43, 14, 19, 19, 'Yet a little while', 'Connection of Jesus'' Presence', 'This connection highlights the theme of Jesus'' temporary presence with his followers. Both passages emphasize the idea of a limited time before Jesus departs, indicating a transition to a new phase of existence for his disciples.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 33, 43, 17, 11, 11, 'Yet a little while am I with you', 'Departure and Divine Protection', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' impending departure from the world and his concern for those he leaves behind. In John 7:33, Jesus indicates he will soon go to the one who sent him, while in John 17:11, he expresses a desire for the protection of his followers as he leaves.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 34, 20, 1, 24, 31, 'ye shall seek me, and shall not find me', 'Seeking and Not Finding', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of seeking God and failing to find Him due to rejection of His counsel. In John 7:34, the inability to come to Him parallels Proverbs 1:28, where those who ignored wisdom will also not find Him when in distress.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 34, 43, 13, 33, 36, 'ye shall seek me', 'Seeking and Following Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of seeking Jesus and the inability to follow Him at that moment. The phrase ''ye shall seek me'' appears in both, linking the disciples'' longing for Jesus to the earlier statement made to the Jews. This connection highlights the continuity of Jesus'' message regarding His presence and departure.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 34, 28, 5, 6, 6, 'shall seek me, and shall not find me', 'Seeking the Lord and Finding Him', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of seeking the Lord but not finding Him. This connection highlights the idea of divine withdrawal, as expressed in both texts.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 34, 42, 13, 34, 35, 'Ye shall seek me, and shall not find me', 'Desolation and Seeking Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of seeking Jesus and the resulting desolation for those who reject him. In John, the statement ''Ye shall seek me, and shall not find me'' reflects the consequences of unfaithfulness seen in Luke''s lament over Jerusalem''s refusal to accept him. This connection highlights the spiritual consequences of rejecting divine guidance.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 34, 43, 8, 21, 24, 'ye shall seek me, and shall not find me', 'Seeking and Inability to Follow', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of seeking Jesus and the inability to follow him. The phrase ''ye shall seek me, and shall not find me'' in John 7:34 is echoed in John 8:21, reinforcing the idea that those who do not believe cannot reach him.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 34, 40, 23, 39, 39, 'Ye shall seek me, and shall not find me', 'Seeking and Not Finding Christ', 'This connection highlights the theme of seeking Jesus and the conditions for seeing Him. In John 7:34, the inability to find Him contrasts with Matthew 23:39, where seeing Him is contingent upon recognizing His authority.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 34, 42, 13, 24, 25, 'shall seek me, and shall not find me', 'Seeking and Not Finding', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of seeking but not finding access to salvation. In John, the inability to find Jesus parallels the futility of seeking to enter the closed door in Luke.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 35, 59, 1, 1, 1, 'dispersed among the Gentiles', 'Connection of Scattered Tribes', 'This connection highlights the theme of dispersion among the Jewish people. John 7:35 mentions the ''dispersed among the Gentiles,'' while James 1:1 addresses ''the twelve tribes which are scattered abroad.''', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 35, 23, 11, 12, 12, 'dispersed among the Gentiles', 'Gathering of the Dispersed', 'Both passages emphasize the gathering of the dispersed, with John referencing the ''dispersed among the Gentiles'' and Isaiah speaking of ''the dispersed of Judah.'' This connection highlights the theme of uniting those who are scattered.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 35, 36, 3, 10, 10, 'dispersed among the Gentiles', 'Dispersed Among the Gentiles', 'This connection highlights the theme of dispersion among the Gentiles. Both passages reference the ''dispersed,'' indicating a shared focus on those scattered among foreign nations.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 35, 60, 1, 1, 1, 'dispersed among the Gentiles', 'Connection of Scattered Believers', 'This connection highlights the theme of dispersion among believers. In John 7:35, the mention of the ''dispersed among the Gentiles'' relates to Peter''s address to ''strangers scattered'' in 1 Peter 1:1.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 35, 43, 12, 20, 20, 'teach the Gentiles', 'Connection of Gentiles in John', 'This connection highlights the presence of Gentiles in both passages. In John 7:35, there is a question about Jesus teaching the Gentiles, while John 12:20 mentions Greeks who came to worship, indicating a fulfillment of that inquiry.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 35, 19, 67, 1, 2, 'teach the Gentiles', 'Connection of Nations and Teaching', 'This connection highlights the theme of teaching among nations. John 7:35 questions whether Jesus will go to the Gentiles, while Psalms 67:2 expresses a desire for God''s way to be known among all nations.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 35, 19, 98, 2, 3, 'teach the Gentiles', 'Connection of Salvation and Gentiles', 'This connection highlights the theme of God''s salvation being revealed to the Gentiles. John 7:35 questions whether Jesus will go to teach the Gentiles, while Psalms 98:2-3 proclaims that God''s righteousness is shown in the sight of the heathen.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 36, 43, 3, 9, 9, 'Ye shall seek me, and shall not find me', 'Seeking Understanding in Dialogue', 'This connection highlights the theme of seeking understanding. In both passages, there is a sense of confusion and the quest for clarity regarding Jesus'' statements.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 36, 43, 7, 34, 34, 'Ye shall seek me, and shall not find me', 'Connection of Seeking and Finding', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of seeking and not finding Jesus. The repetition of the phrase ''Ye shall seek me, and shall not find me'' underscores the significance of this message.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 36, 43, 6, 41, 41, NULL, 'Seeking and Bread from Heaven', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of seeking and misunderstanding Jesus'' identity. In John 7:36, the Jews are confused about where Jesus is going, while in John 6:41, they murmur about his claim of being the bread from heaven, indicating a lack of understanding of his true nature.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 36, 43, 12, 34, 34, 'Ye shall seek me, and shall not find me', 'Seeking and Understanding Christ', 'This connection highlights the theme of seeking Jesus and the confusion surrounding his identity. In both passages, there is a questioning of who Jesus is and the implications of his statements about his presence and departure.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 36, 46, 2, 14, 14, 'Ye shall seek me, and shall not find me', 'Spiritual Discernment and Seeking', 'This connection highlights the theme of seeking understanding. In John 7:36, the inability to find Jesus reflects a lack of spiritual insight, which is echoed in 1 Corinthians 2:14, where the natural man cannot receive spiritual truths.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 37, 23, 55, 1, 1, 'If any man thirst, let him come', 'Invitation to the Thirsty', 'Both passages emphasize an invitation to those who thirst, encouraging them to come and receive sustenance. The call to ''come'' and ''drink'' in John parallels the invitation to ''come ye to the waters'' in Isaiah.', 'theme', 0.72, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 37, 43, 4, 14, 14, 'If any man thirst, let him come', 'Connection of Thirst and Water', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of thirst and the provision of water. In John 7:37, Jesus invites those who thirst to come to Him, while John 4:14 speaks of the water that leads to everlasting life, suggesting a deep spiritual satisfaction.', 'theme', 0.573, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 37, 43, 6, 35, 35, NULL, 'Connection of Thirst and Life', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of spiritual nourishment. In John 7:37, Jesus invites those who thirst to come to Him, while in John 6:35, He states that those who believe in Him will never thirst. This connection highlights the significance of Jesus as the source of both physical and spiritual sustenance.', 'theme', 0.517, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 37, 23, 12, 3, 3, 'If any man thirst, let him come', 'Connection of Thirst and Salvation', 'This connection highlights the theme of spiritual thirst and fulfillment. Both passages emphasize the act of drawing water, symbolizing the reception of salvation and life through Jesus.', 'theme', 0.51, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
